summary: One thing I really liked about Httyd 3 was that it started out with David Tennant (aka Scrooge McDuck and Dr. Who) as a dragon...
body: One thing I really liked about Httyd 3 was that it started out with David Tennant (aka Scrooge McDuck and Dr. Who) as a dragon trapper/ hunter which really made me really quite happy since I am a total Ducktales and Dr. Who fangirl and immediately recognized his voice as soon as he started talking. I also kinda think it sounded like he was also the one who yelled out “To the Chief and Chieftess” at the wedding.

also david tennant with red hair is perfection but they did him dirty with those ugly clumped-together curls he had at the beginning

this is how the hair be looking right after u take out curlers

crowley boo brush it through

that’s my only objection on the whole thing because i wanted to see david tennant with big voluminous waves and instead i got this 12-year-old-me-curling-my-hair-for-the-first-time sadness
